USDA TO HOLD DATA USERS MEETING IN CHICAGO OCT 20 . U . S . Agriculture Department officials will outline upcoming changes in the department ' s statistical and information reports in a meeting with data users in Chicago on Oct 20 , the department said Tuesday . Representatives from the National Agricultural Statistics Service , the Agricultural Marketing Service , the Economic Research , the Foreign Agricultural Service and the World Agricultural Outlook Board will also take comments from users on how USDA can improve its reports . The meeting will take place at the Holiday Inn Mart Plaza . For registration details , see the NASS home page at http : / / www . usda . gov / nass / or contact Fred Vogel at ( 202 ) 720 - 3896 or fvogel @ nass . usda . gov ( ( Washington commodities desk 202 898 8341 ) ) 
